nteracted_element': None}, {'write_file': {'file_name': 'results.md', 'content': '# How to Receive NYC Emergency Alerts on Your Phone\n\n## 1. Register for **Notify NYC** (phone alerts)\n- Call **311** (general inquiries) to sign up.\n- Call **212‑639‑9675** for direct registration.\n- Call **711** if you use Video Relay Service (VRS) for the hearing impaired.\n\n## 2. Install the **Ready NYC** mobile app\n- **iOS (Apple) users:** Download from the App Store.\n- **Android users:** Download from Google Play.\n  The app provides real‑time alerts, preparedness information, and lets you store emergency contacts.\n\n## 3. Enable **Wireless Emergency Alerts (WEA)** on your phone\n- These alerts (e.g., Amber Alerts, severe weather) are automatically sent to all compatible smartphones.\n- Ensure your device’s emergency alert settings are turned **ON** in the system settings.\n\n### Summary of Steps\n1. Call one of the Notify NYC numbers above to register for phone alerts.\n2. Optionally, download the Ready NYC app for richer notifications and preparedness tools.\n3. Verify that your phone’s WEA settings are enabled to receive automatic alerts.\n\nBy following these three actions, you will receive NYC emergency alerts via phone calls, text messages, the Ready NYC app, and automatic wireless alerts.', 'append': False, 'trailing_newline': True, 'leading_newline': False}, 'interacted_element': None}, {'read_file': {'file_name': 'results.md'}, 'interacted_element': None}, {'replace_file_str': {'file_name': 'todo.md', 'old_str': '- [ ] Summarize steps for the user', 'new_str': '- [x] Summarize steps for the user'}, 'interacted_element': None}, {'replace_file_str': {'file_name': 'todo.md', 'old_str': '- [ ] Review and finalize answer', 'new_str': '- [x] Review and finalize answer'}, 'interacted_element': None}, {'done': {'text': 'Here are the steps to receive emergency alerts on your phone in New York City:\n\n1. **Register for Notify NYC**\n   - Call **311** (general inquiries) to sign up.\n   - Call **212‑639‑9675** for direct registration.\n   - Call **711** for Video Relay Service registration.\n   - Alternatively, you can register online via the "Register online for NotifyNYC" link on the Emergency Alerts page.\n\n2. **Download the Ready NYC App**\n   - For iOS devices, download from the Apple App Store (link provided on the page).\n   - For Android devices, download from Google Play (link provided on the page).\n   - The app provides real‑time alerts, preparedness information, and the ability to store emergency contacts.\n\n3. **Enable Wireless Emergency Alerts (WEA)**\n   - Ensure your mobile phone’s emergency alert settings are turned on (usually found in Settings → Notifications → Emergency Alerts).\n   - These alerts are sent automatically by government officials for events like Amber alerts, severe weather, and other emergencies.\n\nBy following these three actions—registering for Notify NYC, installing the Ready NYC app, and enabling WEA—you will receive NYC emergency alerts via phone calls, text messages, the app, and automatic wireless alerts.\n\nThe detailed summary is also available in the attached **results.md** file.', 'success': True, 'files_to_display': ['results.md']}, 'interacted_element': None}, {'done': {'text': 'You can receive emergency alerts on your phone in New\u202fYork\u202fCity by following these steps:\n\n1. **Register for Notify\u202fNYC phone alerts**\n   - Call **311** (general inquiries) to sign up.\n   - Call **212‑639‑9675** for direct registration.\n   - Call **711** if you use Video Relay Service (VRS) for the hearing impaired.\n\n2. **Install the Ready\u202fNYC mobile app**\n   - **iOS users:** Download from the Apple App Store.\n   - **Android users:** Download from Google Play.\n   - The app provides real‑time alerts, preparedness information, and lets you store emergency contacts.\n\n3. **Enable Wireless Emergency Alerts (WEA)** on your phone\n   - These alerts (e.g., Amber Alerts, severe weather) are automatically sent to compatible smartphones.\n   - Ensure your device’s emergency alert settings are turned **ON** in the system settings.\n\nBy completing these three actions—registering via phone, installing the Ready\u202fNYC app, and enabling WEA—you will receive NYC emergency alerts through calls, texts, the app, and automatic wireless alerts.\n\nFor a detailed guide, see the attached **results.md** file.', 'success': True, 'files_to_display': ['results.md']}, 'interacted_element': None}])
